@@ -0,0 +1,303 @@
+# `@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus`
+
+The Reckoner — kit-static petitioner registry, `guild.json` configuration
+parsing, priority dimension types with default-filling, and the
+`reckoner.petition()` / `reckoner.withdraw()` helper APIs.
+
+This package is the foundation that lets petitioners declare themselves and
+emit properly-formed held writs through an ergonomic API. The CDC handler
+that watches held writs and decides their fate (approve / defer / decline)
+is a separate commission that follows this one.
+
+See also: [`docs/architecture/petitioner-registration.md`](../../../docs/architecture/petitioner-registration.md).
+
+---
+
+## Installation
+
+```sh
+pnpm add @shardworks/reckoner-apparatus
+```
+
+Register the apparatus in `guild.json`:
+
+```json
+{
+  "plugins": [
+    "@shardworks/clerk-apparatus",
+    "@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus"
+  ]
+}
+```
+
+The Reckoner must be started after the Clerk (its `requires` declaration
+enforces this automatically).
+
+---
+
+## API
+
+```typescript
+import type { ReckonerApi } from '@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus';
+
+const reckoner = guild().apparatus<ReckonerApi>('reckoner');
+```
+
+### `reckoner.petition(request)` → `Promise<WritDoc>`
+
+Post a writ in `new` phase with Reckoner ext set correctly. This is
+**Workflow 2** — the canonical ergonomic path.
+
+```typescript
+const writ = await reckoner.petition({
+  // Writ fields
+  type:     'mandate',
+  title:    'Address vision drift detected at 04:00 UTC',
+  body:     'Keeper observed 12% drift on nexus vision.',
+  codex:    'nexus',
+  parentId: 'w-...', // optional
+
+  // ext.reckoner fields
+  source:     'vision-keeper.snapshot',
+  priority: {
+    visionRelation: 'vision-violator',
+    severity:       'serious',
+    scope:          'major-area',
+    time:           { decay: true, deadline: null },
+    domain:         ['quality'],
+  },
+  complexity: 'bounded',     // optional
+  payload:    { ... },       // opaque petitioner data, optional
+  labels:     { 'vision-keeper.io/vision-id': 'nexus' }, // optional
+});
+// writ.phase === 'new'
+// writ.ext?.reckoner === { source, priority, complexity?, payload?, labels? }
+```
+
+`petition()` performs, in order:
+
+1. Validates `source` against the petitioner registry (subject to
+   `enforceRegistration` configuration).
+2. Applies contract defaults for any omitted `priority` dimensions:
+   `vision-neutral / minor / minor-area / {decay: false, deadline: null} / []`.
+3. Validates all five priority dimension values against their schema.
+4. Calls `clerk.post()` to create the writ.
+5. Writes `ext.reckoner` via `clerk.setWritExt()`.
+6. Returns the final `WritDoc`.
+
+### `reckoner.withdraw(writId, reason?)` → `Promise<WritDoc>`
+
+Withdraw a held writ — transition it to `cancelled`. Thin wrapper around
+`clerk.transition(writId, 'cancelled', { resolution: reason })`.
+
+```typescript
+await reckoner.withdraw(writId, 'Snapshot superseded by newer drift.');
+```
+
+No source-check is performed — any caller may withdraw any writ via this
+helper. The purpose is ergonomic discoverability, not enforcement.
+
+### `reckoner.getRegisteredSources()` → `ReadonlyArray<PetitionerDescriptor>`
+
+Return all sources registered via `petitioners` kit contributions. Sealed
+after startup. Useful for operator / observability tooling.
+
+```typescript
+const sources = reckoner.getRegisteredSources();
+// [{ source: 'vision-keeper.snapshot', description: '...' }, ...]
+```
+
+---
+
+## Configuration
+
+Configure the Reckoner under the `reckoner` key in `guild.json`:
+
+```json
+{
+  "reckoner": {
+    "enforceRegistration": false,
+    "disabledSources": []
+  }
+}
+```
+
+### `enforceRegistration` (boolean, default `false`)
+
+Controls behaviour when a petition's `source` is not in the registry:
+
+- `false` — log a warning and proceed. Emergent petitioners that haven't
+  registered yet still get their writs created.
+- `true` — decline the petition with an error; no writ is posted. Guards
+  against typos and abandoned sources.
+
+### `disabledSources` (string array, default `[]`)
+
+Per-source disable list. Petitions from any source in this array are skipped
+by the Reckoner (left in `new` phase with no reckoning entry). Removing a
+source from the list resumes normal consideration of pending writs.
+
+```json
+{
+  "reckoner": {
+    "disabledSources": ["tech-debt.detected"]
+  }
+}
+```
+
+---
+
+## Kit Interface
+
+Petitioners declare themselves via the `petitioners` kit contribution:
+
+```typescript
+// In a plugin's kit (or apparatus's supportKit)
+export default {
+  kit: {
+    requires: ['reckoner'],
+    petitioners: [
+      {
+        source:      'vision-keeper.snapshot',
+        description: 'Vision-vs-reality snapshots emitted when the keeper ' +
+                     'observes drift worth surfacing.',
+      },
+    ],
+  },
+};
+```
+
+```typescript
+interface PetitionerDescriptor {
+  /** Format: `{pluginId}.{kebab-suffix}`. Must be prefixed with the contributing plugin id. */
+  source:      string;
+  /** Human-readable one-liner for operators. */
+  description: string;
+}
+```
+
+### Source-id grammar
+
+Source ids must be `{pluginId}.{kebab-suffix}`:
+
+- Both segments are kebab-case (lowercase letters, digits, single hyphens;
+  no leading or trailing hyphens).
+- The prefix **must** match the contributing plugin's id.
+- Malformed ids fail at guild startup, never silently at first emit.
+
+Valid examples: `vision-keeper.snapshot`, `patron-bridge.commission`,
+`tech-debt.detected`.
+
+### Collision policy
+
+Two `petitioners` entries with the same `source` string are a hard startup
+error — the Reckoner refuses to start with a diagnostic naming both
+contributing plugin ids. This mirrors the framework-wide collision rule
+applied to writ-types, rig-template-mappings, and engine designs.
+
+---
+
+## Types
+
+### `Priority`
+
+Five-axis priority schema:
+
+```typescript
+type Priority = {
+  visionRelation:
+    | 'vision-blocker'   // vision is unreachable without this
+    | 'vision-violator'  // current state actively diverges from the vision
+    | 'vision-advancer'  // pushes toward an aspirational aspect
+    | 'vision-neutral';  // operational / hygiene / research
+  severity:
+    | 'critical'   // production breakage, agents blocked
+    | 'serious'    // significant degradation, daily workarounds
+    | 'moderate'   // noticeable but tolerable
+    | 'minor';     // cosmetic, convenience, polish
+  scope:
+    | 'whole-product'  // every user / every commission
+    | 'major-area'     // a major feature or subsystem
+    | 'minor-area';    // a small slice or one workflow
+  time: {
+    decay:    boolean;         // urgency grows over time
+    deadline: string | null;   // ISO date or null
+  };
+  domain: Array<DomainTag>;  // multi-valued classification
+};
+
+type DomainTag =
+  | 'security' | 'compliance' | 'cost' | 'feature' | 'quality'
+  | 'infrastructure' | 'documentation' | 'research' | 'ergonomics';
+```
+
+### `ComplexityTier`
+
+Petitioner-side coarse cost estimate (optional; omit rather than guess):
+
+```typescript
+type ComplexityTier =
+  | 'mechanical'   // ~50K–200K tokens
+  | 'bounded'      // ~200K–1M tokens
+  | 'exploratory'  // ~1M–5M tokens
+  | 'open-ended';  // 5M+ tokens
+```
+
+### `defaultPriority(partial?)`
+
+Apply contract defaults for any omitted dimensions:
+
+```typescript
+import { defaultPriority } from '@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus';
+
+const p = defaultPriority({ visionRelation: 'vision-violator' });
+// p.severity === 'minor', p.scope === 'minor-area', etc.
+```
+
+### `validateSourceId(source)`
+
+Return `true` when `source` matches the `{pluginId}.{kebab-suffix}` grammar:
+
+```typescript
+import { validateSourceId } from '@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus';
+
+validateSourceId('vision-keeper.snapshot'); // true
+validateSourceId('no-dot');                 // false
+```
+
+---
+
+## Workflow 1 — Direct post (always available)
+
+Petitioners that prefer to call `clerk.post()` directly obtain identical
+Reckoner behavior. The `petition()` helper is a convenience layer, not a
+gate:
+
+```typescript
+await clerk.post({
+  type:     'mandate',
+  title:    'Address vision drift detected at 04:00 UTC',
+  body:     '...',
+  codex:    'nexus',
+  parentId: 'w-...',
+});
+await clerk.setWritExt(writ.id, 'reckoner', {
+  source:    'vision-keeper.snapshot',
+  priority: {
+    visionRelation: 'vision-violator',
+    severity:       'serious',
+    scope:          'major-area',
+    time:           { decay: true, deadline: null },
+    domain:         ['quality'],
+  },
+  complexity: 'bounded',
+});
+```
+
+---
+
+## Dependencies
+
+- **Required:** `@shardworks/clerk-apparatus` — `petition()` and `withdraw()`
+  call Clerk APIs; the Reckoner `requires: ['clerk']` in its apparatus
+  declaration.
